ns with striking universities unions and ensure that public universities resume for normal activities. Details later:   By Victor Ahiuma-Young The Nigeria Union of Petroleum and Natural Gas Workers, NUPENG, yesterday vowed to join the solidarity strike being planned by the Nigeria Labour Congress, NLC, over a protracted strike by the Academic Staff Union of Universities, ASUU and other Unions in the nation’s tertiary institutions. Among other… In "News" Varsity strike: Why FG rejects Report of Briggs Committee, Presidency Source In "News" INDICATION emerged yesterday that the Federal Government may have rejected the Nimi-Briggs Committee report, following alleged allocation of pay rise of 180 per cent to university teaching staff, while the non teaching staff were given only 10 per cent. In "Don't Miss"